<Review ID>0980200
<Product Name>Creative Zen V Plus 2 GB Portable Media Player (Black/Green)
<Title>super MP3 player!
<Date>Thu Jan 25 00:00:00 CST 2007
<Content>tiny is the word,..which means I almost always have it on me, which is the whole idea. It's more compact than the rival Sansa, which is why I chose this player. Also, I really loved my Zen Micro,..so, after two years, I gave it to my boy and got this.   Software is excellent, even better than the Zen Micro. Love that drag and drop simplicity,..what could be better? It's so tiny, it just hangs round my neck and I don't even know it's there.  Perfect. Plus, the Zen sig/noise ratio is excellent: the clarity will spoil you so that you'll never be able to enjoy an ipod again. I mean, you can easily hear the fingers slipping up and down guitar strings with this.   I never read the manual, or had to refer to it. I'm not happy with having a non user-replaceable battery,..that almost drove me to buy the Sansa. But, in the end, I chose this MP3 player for the tiny size and the incomparable clarity. If you're into sound specs, do the research and you'll see what I'm talking about.    I put a slideshow of about 50 pix of my kids on it,..it's cool, and easy to do. I work a 12 hour grave-yard shift, and the battery lasts that long easily. I listen to audio books all night, so I need the bookmarks and the resume play features of the Zen. I use a 1 dollar earbud with one side cut off,..so it just runs up my collar to one ear,..I told the people at work it's a hearing aid,..and management is so scared about getting sued for harassing me for my "disability" they leave me and Dickens alone. (no PC? I just borrowed Pickwick Papers from the library,..and pumped it in via the line-in,..all 12 CD's,..and it sorted itself out, all set to go. )  
<Overall>5

