<Review ID>5958767
<Product Name>Creative Zen V Plus 2 GB Portable Media Player (Black/Green)
<Title>Zen V Plus Reciew
<Date>Wed Feb 07 00:00:00 CST 2007
<Content>The Zen V Plus is a great product. It is the same weight as an ipod nano so techincally they're the same size. Music quality is exellent. The Video quality seems a little choppy, but really isnt that bad. This player can also be used for working-out without any skipping at all. My player froze once when i first connected without installing the software, but it has never given me problems since. The scratch resistant surface is also a great improvement of the zem vision: m. I'll list the main pros and cons  Pros: FM radio, voice recorder, line-in recording, very small size, scratch-resistant surface, great audio quality, does nearly everything a Vision: M can do  Cons: Video quality could be better in terms of space used for it and fps, joystick may be hard to use for people who have large thumbs, no user-replaceable battery  Although i don't think the lack of a user replaceable battery is a big deal, many people do. In the end this player is something you should definitly get over the ipod nano, sansa, and clix in terms of size and overall quality.  
<Overall>5

